  "prompt": "Why was the Pakistan national anthem sung first in the India-Pakistan World Cup match?",
  "response": "In international cricket matches, including those in the World Cup, the national anthems of both competing teams are typically played before the start of the game. The order in which the national anthems are sung can vary and is often decided by the match organizers or based on mutual agreement between the two teams.\n\nIn the specific instance of the India-Pakistan World Cup match where the Pakistan national anthem was sung first, it could have been due to organizational logistics, rotational protocols, or a decision made by the host country or the International Cricket Council (ICC). There is no fixed rule that mandates one anthem must always precede the other, so the order can differ from match to match.\n\nIt's important to note that such arrangements are usually made to ensure fairness and respect for both teams, and the order of the anthems does not carry any political or symbolic significance.",
